New Records: Morocco equalled the biggest winning margin in 2025 qualifying after South Africa set the benchmark with a five-goal drubbing of Congo.
Key Match Events: Azzedine Ounahi netted twice and Abde Ezzalzouli, Achraf Hakimi and Soufiane Rahimi once each as Morocco eased to victory.
Pre-Game Insights: It was a predictable Group B outcome as 114 places separate top-ranked African team Morocco from the Central African Republic.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Morocco qualify automatically for the AFCON as hosts, with the tournament due to start on December 21st 2025 and finish on January 18th, 2026.
Instead of playing friendlies, Morocco opted for competitive match practice.
